Kenya Power Seeks 25% Increase in Electricity Tariffs, Business Daily Says

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-06-29T04:08:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/kenya-power-seeks-25-increase-in-electricity-tariffs-business-daily-says.html
Kenya Power Ltd., the East African
nation’s sole electricity distributor, is seeking regulatory
approval to increase its tariffs by as much as 25 percent,
Business Daily reported.  The proposed increase would raise monthly consumer power
bills by an average of 400 shillings ($4.44), the Nairobi-based
newspaper said, citing people it didn’t identify.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  